com.sap.cloud.sdk.cloudplatform.servicebinding

Class ServiceOperatorSecretRootKeyFileSystemStructureParsingStrategy

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sap.cloud.sdk.cloudplatform.servicebinding.ServiceOperatorSecretRootKeyFileSystemStructureParsingStrategy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FileSystemServiceBindingLoader.ParsingStrategy

    @Beta
public class ServiceOperatorSecretRootKeyFileSystemStructureParsingStrategy
extends Object
    Concrete implementation of the FileSystemServiceBindingLoader.ParsingStrategy interface that is capable of transforming the default file system structure into service bindings based on a single file that has been created by the ServiceOperator (e.g. in a K8s cluster), using the "SecretRootKey" behavior.
    This implementation assumes that there is exactly a single file that contains a JsonObject, which in turn contains all service binding properties on the root level.

        If null, the DEFAULT_BACKUP_PROPERTY_SETTER is used.
        charset - The charset to decode individual files.
        If null, the FileSystemServiceBindingLoader.DEFAULT_CHARSET is used.
